Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.48,0:03:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.27,0:03:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.52,0:03:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.35,0:03:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no kitchen cleaver with a deep red handle here, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.72,0:03:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.78,0:03:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's the situation we find ourselves in...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.81,0:03:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know anything about a kitchen cleaver with a red handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.75,0:03:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were probably led astray because you wanted to see me as a\Nmountain witch, and that's why you witnessed such an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.55,0:03:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I'm certain, with my own eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.47,0:03:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.64,0:03:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We will now thoroughly search this house, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.85,0:03:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If everyone would stand by in a back room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.60,0:03:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, we're going, Yoshida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.74,0:03:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.69,0:03:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.20,0:03:58.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hammer for pounding in the tent pegs is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.58,0:03:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hammer?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.87,0:04:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bag was left unattended in the hallway, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.08,0:04:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the culprit used it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hammer can't cut a person's neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.38,0:04:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.30,0:04:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go and ask the detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.51,0:04:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.18,0:04:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as far as a hammer, we found one in the forest near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.23,0:04:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fairly new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.19,0:04:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.15,0:04:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you should investigate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.36,0:04:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the culprit may have used it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.28,0:04:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But hammers aren't blades, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.99,0:04:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, have you investigated that box?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we haven't yet got to the boxes in this area...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.17,0:04:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't this a kitchen knife!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.76,0:04:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A kitchen knife with a red handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.60,0:05:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this the one Mitsuhiko saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been very well maintained, and there\Naren't any nicks or scratches on it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.89,0:05:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Below the knife maker's signature, a name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.69,0:05:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouta?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.98,0:05:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouta was, if I remember correctly,\Nthat old woman's grandson...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.24,0:05:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No reaction?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.61,0:05:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no reaction to the luminol?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, not from the cutlery from this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.53,0:05:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nor from the camp tools you all brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.83,0:05:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, even from that kitchen knife\Nwith the red handle, there were no traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.79,0:05:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you went through all that trouble to find it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.67,0:05:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.05,0:05:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.76,0:05:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, you all...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you play in the mud or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Play in the mud?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found traces of multiple people from this\Nhousehold having walked around with muddy feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.85,0:05:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Muddy footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.19,0:05:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moving the body without permission,\Nwalking around with muddy feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.86,0:05:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, it makes it hard for us, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.19,0:05:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:05:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of muddy feet, if I remember correctly, at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.70,0:06:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma's feet were bare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fuuga's feet were as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.46,0:06:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also ran out with bare feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.08,0:06:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Raito person...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.63,0:06:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Raito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:13.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fuuga!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.51,0:06:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was wearing shoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.51,0:06:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.97,0:06:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.84,0:06:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.89,0:06:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goldfish are thirsty, so I felt sorry for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.14,0:06:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, last night the water in this tank\Nwas filled up to this mark, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.85,0:06:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a lot lower now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.23,0:06:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the goldfish felt hot, and drank a lot of water, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.24,0:06:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.45,0:06:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the culprit took the hammer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.41,0:06:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Ayumi got water from the tap...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.87,0:06:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't do that, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.08,0:06:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you put that water in which hasn't had the chlorine extracted...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.04,0:06:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll actually be bad for the goldfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.46,0:06:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the goldfish are expending so\Nmuch energy to keep watch over it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.59,0:06:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't disturb the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.38,0:06:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keeping watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.63,0:07:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.84,0:07:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapon which has been in use since\Nancient times, over its location, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.68,0:07:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.93,0:07:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the results...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.10,0:07:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapons in this house, or in other words the weapons\Nowned by you all, all show no luminol reaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:17.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is to say, there is no trace at all of\Nblood having been on any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.82,0:07:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Additionally, after everyone rushed to the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.78,0:07:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is after Ooba Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had the carotid artery\Nin her neck slashed with a blade and screamed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.03,0:07:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one left this house, and based on that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.91,0:07:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that it's impossible to have left with the weapon, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone is innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.21,0:07:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what it comes down to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.71,0:07:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, in that case, we won't have to\Nundergo the police interview either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.22,0:07:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.88,0:07:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For further investigation, we'd like to hear\Neveryone's stories, so we'd like to consult with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.22,0:07:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we could trouble you all to come to the station at a later date...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.97,0:07:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I'll only be used as a reference, I'm fine with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.77,0:07:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.73,0:07:55.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened as far as the kitchen knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:08:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} found it for us\Nin a box made of paulownia wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.40,0:08:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As to why you kept silent about that kitchen knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.53,0:08:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll ask you about it in detail at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.91,0:08:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just forgot about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, I am getting on in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.37,0:08:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, how did the culprit escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.00,0:08:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any weird footprints left around the\Nhouse except for in front of the entrance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.05,0:08:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that'd be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.97,0:08:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking it's quite certain the culprit used some sort of trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.39,0:08:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite natural that there were no footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.98,0:08:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because both the culprit and the weapon are still inside this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.52,0:08:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if you're gonna use my voice, at least tell me before you start!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You surprised me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.03,0:08:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, if I could have a word...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We police have searched this house thoroughly and found\Nnothing, so where would you say the weapon is hidden?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.25,0:08:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't that you haven't found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.42,0:08:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that you haven't searched for it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.38,0:09:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because that weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.05,0:09:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was an object the culprit made by changing the shape\Nof something originally from this house into a blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.80,0:09:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In appearance, it looks nothing like a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.76,0:09:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Changed the shape?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something originally from this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.39,0:09:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.94,0:09:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're talking about something that was\Noriginally in this house having been used...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.11,0:09:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means the culprit is someone\Nwho's familiar with this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the culprit really was the inhabitant\Nof this house, that old woman, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.53,0:09:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.78,0:09:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as someone that's lived in this house for nearly\Ntwenty years, there's one other person here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.08,0:09:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.58,0:09:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.13,0:09:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The grandson of this old woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.54,0:09:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kahara Fuuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Fuuga, is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.09,0:09:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.97,0:09:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.89,0:09:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you were asked where the washroom was in\Nthis house, you replied immediately, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.43,0:09:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remembered!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.10,0:09:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I used it last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.23,0:10:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why did you say those words?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.36,0:10:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those words?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.27,0:10:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it when you guys first came to this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.32,0:10:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Boy, is someone from this house here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.49,0:10:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means you knew that I wasn't one\Nof the children from this house, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.62,0:10:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.71,0:10:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I was asked by that grandson guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.46,0:10:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To come and check up on his grandmother that he\Nhadn't seen in a while, to see if she was doing well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.47,0:10:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I heard that the old woman was living alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.30,0:10:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, how come you knew about the goldfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.22,0:10:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goldfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.31,0:10:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.23,0:10:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That, "Out of these twelve, the Tamasaba is the only\None of a variety that you don't get to see very often."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:44.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I said it, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I used to have goldfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.86,0:10:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as what variety of goldfish it is, I'd know just by seeing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not the variety...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.83,0:10:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The number?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.83,0:10:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you know about goldfish...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.66,0:11:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To know at a glance that there are twelve\Nof them swimming around in the tank...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.88,0:11:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would know except for the\Nperson who owns the goldfish, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.46,0:11:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.59,0:11:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's certainly true, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.09,0:11:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.00,0:11:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.39,0:11:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.60,0:11:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be that getting lost, running\Nout of gas, and coming here was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.77,0:11:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.19,0:11:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did it on purpose to check up on his grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.19,0:11:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having undergone cosmetic surgery for his face,\Nhe thought that he wouldn't be found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.99,0:11:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.95,0:11:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why you were extremely reluctant\Nto undergo police questioning was because...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.53,0:11:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the culprit, isn't that right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.04,0:11:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.75,0:11:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:41.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.62,0:11:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it was to hide his real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.63,0:11:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Raito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you were about to say something\Nwhen Fuuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got all riled up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.47,0:11:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.47,0:11:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to say what my real name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:11:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Adachi Raito is a name that I am known by at the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.31,0:12:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's a professional name, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.23,0:12:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, your name is as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.23,0:12:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.06,0:12:08.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in order to break that line of questioning, he got\Nall riled up about having to undergo questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.07,0:12:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What Fuuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted to hide was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.53,0:12:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that he was in fact Tanaka Iwae's grandson, Tanaka Shouta.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.91,0:12:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you're saying it was because he wanted to hide\Nhis real name, then Fuuga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.84,0:12:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But earlier, you said that the culprit skillfully\Nused something from this house, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.17,0:12:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because even if one isn't familiar with this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an object that, as long as one recognizes what\Nit is upon sight, it can be utilized as a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.39,0:12:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use that certain thing and the\Nhammer that was stolen from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.44,0:12:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hammer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.56,0:12:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, wasn't Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} worried about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.07,0:12:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi was?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.28,0:12:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were wondering if the reason the water level in the fish tank had\Ndropped since last night was due to the goldfish drinking the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.70,0:12:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, in actuality, it wasn't because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.54,0:13:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means that something was\Ntaken out from the fish tank, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.12,0:13:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what is that "something"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.96,0:13:10.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's something that, in the distant past, in the Joumon Era...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.17,0:13:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was often used as a weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.67,0:13:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obsidian!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.34,0:13:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obsidian, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.38,0:13:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.34,0:13:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you break it apart, you'll end up with\Nfairly sharp blade-like fragments.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit used that, and cut through Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.23,0:13:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obsidian into a blade?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.56,0:13:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Le's see, and then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.15,0:13:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was used to break it apart was my hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place it was broken apart was in the forest\Nwhere my hammer was reportedly found...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order for no one to be able to hear the loud\Nnoise produced when breaking it apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.74,0:13:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit likely made the weapon last night\Nsometime, before the rain began to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.71,0:13:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there were no footprints left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.38,0:14:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.46,0:14:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.34,0:14:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who did all that, the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.51,0:14:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would be the person who looked at the rocks in the\Nfish tank and immediately identified them as obsidian...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.18,0:14:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Adachi Raito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.51,0:14:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.52,0:14:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hold on a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To say I'm the culprit because I'm familiar with rocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.23,0:14:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the rocks were obsidian...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.28,0:14:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This old woman, and her apparent grandson\NFuuga, would both know that as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.61,0:14:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why would you say it was me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What first drew my attention to you was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.04,0:14:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.41,0:14:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When hearing the scream of a woman familiar to you coming\Nfrom outside, and then while rushing to the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.09,0:14:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think there would be anyone\Nwho would put their shoes on first?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Putting on shoes requires time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.97,0:14:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a case where the entrance is not level with\Nthe rest of the house, like in this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.97,0:14:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd have to first find your own shoes, place\Nyour feet in, and then slip your heels inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.06,0:15:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that sort of situation, one wouldn't put on their shoes, but would\Nrush to the door to check on the situation in their bare feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.94,0:15:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the old woman, and the grandson did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.32,0:15:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, not only did you have your high-top shoes on\Nfirmly, you also had your shoelaces properly tied.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.49,0:15:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, you didn't rush to the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were there in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.50,0:15:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that indicates you murdered Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.26,0:15:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand how that's suspicious, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.13,0:15:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To know for sure that he's the culprit\Njust because he had his shoes on...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.64,0:15:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said it before, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.18,0:15:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the shoes were just what drew my attention to Raito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.10,0:15:38.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drew your attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.27,0:15:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deciding factor was the hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.31,0:15:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hammer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.65,0:15:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we still don't know who stole it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make the weapon, the old woman or the grandson\Nwould have just used something that was originally in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, something from the toolbox that was in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:16:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't have lingered in the hallway, where\Nsomeone could have come out at any time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.12,0:16:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To take a hammer from my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.67,0:16:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that's certainly true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.55,0:16:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In such a situation, it would be easy to narrow down\Nthe suspects to those who were related to the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.39,0:16:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something probably happened last night that\Ncaused you to resolve to commit murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.52,0:16:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.23,0:16:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what excuse you used, but\Nyou invited Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} outside with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And because she didn't hear any quarrelling voices nor any\Nsuspicious sounds, Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} agreed and left her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You both made your way in the dark to the\Nentrance without anyone noticing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.83,0:16:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put on your shoes at the entrance, and were\Nabout to go outside when something happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.75,0:16:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what would that something be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had been obediently\Nfollowing directions up until that point...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.59,0:16:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noticed that it was raining outside and decided\Nthat she didn't want to go outside, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.01,0:16:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the sound of Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} running up the stairs\Nthat made him feel as if the situation took an abrupt turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.14,0:16:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are you able to tell, to that extent?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.10,0:17:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If not for that, the incident wouldn't\Nhave occurred in front of the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:06.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't have been in the plan to murder her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.36,0:17:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nervous, you decided to kill her there, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.32,0:17:13.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if you had tripped into her, you dragged her outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.15,0:17:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And sliced her neck open with the weapon\Nyou had hidden on you, killing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.66,0:17:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, you left Akane san's body\Nthere, returned to the entrance...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.37,0:17:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after opening the door, returned\Nonce again to the body's side...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sweeping Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s remains up into your arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.09,0:17:38.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make it look as if he had rushed\Nto the scene after hearing her scream...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.43,0:17:40.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He camouflaged the true nature of the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.89,0:17:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because he had no way to hide the blood\Nthat had gotten onto his clothes and his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.48,0:17:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where, then, is the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.56,0:17:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you haven't found it yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.69,0:17:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then perhaps it's inside the fish tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:18:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because before you went to the washroom, saying you\Nwanted to wash off her blood, you touched the fish tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.16,0:18:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's likely when you put it inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.37,0:18:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you didn't have time to wipe it\Noff, they should still be on the stone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.92,0:18:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood, and your fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.22,0:18:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having had it explained like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.72,0:18:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.55,0:18:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.14,0:18:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.81,0:18:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For those goldfish, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goldfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.56,0:18:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, it really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.48,0:18:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to kill that sort of woman, I disturbed their home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For you as a host, she was an important customer, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had already planned to quit being a host very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since my parents had finally gotten enough money together\Nto repay the loan they had taken from her father's company.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But last night, that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.34,0:18:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.88,0:18:57.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's being inflated to about three times as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I recommended a stock to Raito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s parents that\Nseemed like it'd go up, they went right along with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.18,0:19:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder how their faces look now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.73,0:19:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the president of the company that issued those\Nstocks was arrested and the stock price plunged...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.44,0:19:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I really should direct much of my gratitude toward God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of this, Raito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will be my manservant for life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To break off from that woman who said those words...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I only became a host out of\Nnecessity in order to repay that debt...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.92,0:19:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as I had expected, it was an uphill battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.04,0:19:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've always been an old-fashioned sort of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.05,0:19:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sort of job where I served women is not who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.68,0:19:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I never expected my way of being old-fashioned\Nwould have extended to my choice of weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.53,0:19:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you could take care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.58,0:19:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.98,0:19:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about this kitchen knife with the red handle?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.36,0:20:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of returning that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.07,0:20:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.54,0:20:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could I please take a look at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.33,0:20:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.96,0:20:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.25,0:20:16.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.21,0:20:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, young man...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.67,0:20:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you know my grandson, would you please tell him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.64,0:20:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he doesn't need to worry about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.85,0:20:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that his own body...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.23,0:20:33.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His own body is the only thing he needs to take care of for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.44,0:20:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of telling him that, could I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.28,0:20:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could I take this kitchen knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.66,0:20:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I'm sure he'd be delighted to receive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.16,0:20:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, please do so for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old woman knew he was her grandson?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.76,0:21:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.22,0:21:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely why she hid that kitchen knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.89,0:21:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she'd planned to give it to her\Ngrandson when he came back as a fine chef...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.01,0:21:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a precious kitchen knife that she sharpened every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.23,0:21:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she really was sharpening it with a scary demonic face...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same as the Hannya mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.61,0:21:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a scary face, but you can also see\Nhow it's a sad face as well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.70,0:21:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have been desperately sharpening it\Nwhile trying to hold together her broken heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.20,0:21:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Entrusting to that blade her faint hopes that her grandson...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.66,0:21:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who had changed in both appearance and aspiration...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.75,0:21:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could possibly return to his original path.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.46,0:21:44.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the light from the mountain witch's cutlery...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.05,0:21:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the light from the sad tears of the old\Nwoman who thinks of her grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.78,0:23:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A month later, at a Japanese restaurant I visited with Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.49,0:23:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw a young chef being yelled at.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.50,0:23:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're slow, Tanaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.50,0:23:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you filleted it yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.83,0:23:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.88,0:23:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A young chef with a face I recognized\Nwas filleting fish with all his might...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.84,0:23:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grasping tightly in his hand a kitchen knife with a red handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.14,0:23:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eventually, he'll surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.75,0:23:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.57,0:23:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're slow, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.65,0:23:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you decided yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.44,0:23:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought she was a Hannya for a moment there...
